On January 5, 2021, the President signed four bills into law. The first is the "Protecting Families of Fallen Servicemembers Act," which extends certain protections under the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act to individuals for termination of contracts for telephone, multichannel video programming, or internet access service. The second is the "1921 Silver Dollar Coin Anniversary Act," which requires the Department of the Treasury to mint and issue coins in honor of the 100th anniversary of the completion of coinage of the Morgan dollar and the 100th anniversary of the commencement of coinage of the Peace dollar. The third is the "Combating Pandemic Scams Act of 2020," which mandates the Federal Trade Commission to develop and share information with the public regarding scams related to the COVID-19 pandemic. Lastly, the "Servicemembers and Veterans Initiative Act of 2020" establishes the Servicemembers and Veterans Initiative within the Civil Rights Division of the Justice Department.